        {
          "scid": "an4.227:1.1",
          "pli": "… pe … Adiṭṭhe diṭṭhavādī hoti, asute sutavādī hoti, amute mutavādī hoti, aviññāte viññātavādī hoti … pe … adiṭṭhe adiṭṭhavādī hoti, asute asutavādī hoti, amute amutavādī hoti, aviññāte aviññātavādī hoti … pe …. ",
          "en": "“A foolish person … makes much bad karma. … They say they’ve seen, heard, thought, or known something, but they haven’t. … An astute person … makes much merit. … They say they haven’t seen, heard, thought, or known something, and they haven’t. …” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an4.227:1.2",
          "pli": "Sattamaṃ. ",
